After learning all the trusted CAs in your network a private trust store is built to validate all TLS encrypted sessions going Certificates that fail validation will be flagged along with the device using Encryption Modernization Encryption is the foundation of information security, and keeps your data from being accessed, exfiltrated, disclosed, or Our encryption visibility technology will proactively assess the strength of the security protocols being used to ensure your data is being transmitted safely and Periodically over the last few years the NSA has updated their list of obsolete encryption Keeping up with what encryption algorithms and ciphers are actively being used in your network is critical to securing your data in Our technology will monitor the negotiated TLS sessions in your network and ensure they are using the latest modernized Identity Exposure Identity is traditionally established by providing a username, and a password that proves the user’s These credentials are the keys to accessing most digital assets in our corporate networks Unfortunately, operating system vendors continue to leverage insecure protocols for user authentication, and are exposing our credentials in cleartext, open to replay and MITM Seeing cleartext usernames and weakly hashed passwords on the network, gives you clear insight into how easy it is for hackers get access and escalated privileges in recent publicized Our identity domain risk provides you with a list of authentication exposures in your network, so you can quickly remediate any Database Anomaly Detection Databases are the vaults business use to store private information, like PII, PHI and The first databases systems were developed long before the adoption of the IP protocol, so the protocols they use today are Unlike other client server protocols, database protocols multiplex multiple database instance communication on a single Our database visibility technology was developed to decode these custom protocols so they can be effectively managed and When you hear about security breaches with billions of records being exposed, you can be sure that the attack most likely involved a We Gluon Digital Gluon Blog - Why I Started Gluon Digital Home Our Mission Services About us Blog What is a Gluon? Contact Us Gluon Digital Offical carrier of the Strong Why I Started Gluon Digital Author: David Masri Founder & CEO A bit of background From the moment I decided to change my major to computer information systems (away from finance) I knew I wanted to work with A big part of it was the data processing course I I found a beauty in data theory that was unmatched in my other computer science It may very well be because at the time Baruch College (CUNY) decided to teach Java over C++, which was in its infancy, and the textbook assigned was horrendously full of errors (which could make any new programmer want to cry – there was no Stack overflow to help!). Contrary to the Java textbook, I found the data processing textbook to be brilliantly It is in fact the only one of my college text books I still have (and a quick look online shows that it lasted the test of time, it’s up to the edition !). By the time I joined the Salesforce Ohana (with Redkite in late ) I had spent years working with data and various enterprise systems (ERP, , BI, CRM, Data Warehousing ). I was running a large Salesforce project, for a very large financial services firm, that included a complex data migration component from a CRM The process being used to do this migration seemed to break every rule and best practice I could think But what really caught me by surprise, was that when I questioned the process, I was told “This is how everyone does it, it’s the standard process”. Of course, I didn’t believe that, so I did my own research, low and behold, they were telling the truth, the entire Salesforce community, or at least the ones writing about it online, were following insane data migration I wrapped up that project, and then spent the next year or so completely changing how we (Redkite) did data migrations (and to a lesser, but still substantial extent, integrations). Two years and two acquisitions later, I was running a small team of data experts within Liquidhub Capgemini overseeing all of the data work within the Salesforce Not long after, I joined Silverline and was putting together a training program for the data team based on the patterns and best practices I used to train my team at Capgemini, when I realized I had all the content I needed to fill a book, and then With the encouragement of my manager, I signed a contract with Apress and in December , my book Developing Data Migrations and Integrations with Salesforce: Patterns and Best Practices was A book I felt, and still feel the Salesforce Ohana sorely I had a mission to fix how the Salesforce Ohana works with, and thinks about Gluon Digital is a direct extension of that In fact our mission statement is: To clean up the world s CRM data, by educating the Salesforce Ohana on data best practices, and leading by example to prove those best practices Strong data makes Salesforce Our services are directly related to Our Mission: We educate the Salesforce Ohana on data best practices, by: Sharing knowledge on the Salesforce Data Blog . The only blog exclusively dedicated to Salesforce and Regularly speaking on various topics regarding Salesforce data quality, strategy, migrations, and And of course by promoting my book Developing Data Migrations and Integrations with We lead by example to prove those best practices work by: Partnering with our clients to tackle the most complex Salesforce data Helping them devise an overall data strategy, clean up existing data, migrate their data to Salesforce and build We partner with Salesforce SIs (System Integrators) who are tired of having data issues and failed migrations causing project We can either partner with your delivery organization to train them on properly performing data migrations, or we can act as and outsourced white labeled data migration department, handling all your data migrations, and guaranteeing We are not a Salesforce SI, we don’t compete with Salesforce SIs, we partner with If you are sick of data migrations causing your projects to fail, and negatively impacting your brand, please, reach out . Why the name “Gluon Digital”, What is a Gluon anyway? I have always loved physics, so I wanted to name my company after something from the world of Gluons, being strong force carrier particles made it an obvious (though it took me quite some time to realize that). Care Reform By Natalie Missakian , January , :00 AM Sharon Echtman, , of Deep River, is advocating for greater rights for nursing home residents and their Photo by Christopher Capozziello Before the coronavirus pandemic, Sharon Echtman visited her husband, Joseph, , who is legally blind and has Alzheimer’s disease, at his nursing home twice a Echtman, , of Deep River, took him for walks and car rides, brought him food and made sure he ate and But when the state banned visitors at care facilities in March, his condition deteriorated “From March to July he lost over pounds,” she “He wasn’t He was in a He had terrible anxiety issues and ” Connecticut began allowing indoor visits in September, requiring that visitors wear masks, practice hand hygiene and maintain six feet of distance from others, among other But some family caregivers say nursing homes haven’t been consistently following state and federal More than of the state’s coronavirus deaths have been in care facilities, compared with a national rate of around AARP Connecticut is urging state lawmakers to put care reform at the top of the agenda during this year’s legislative A working group that includes patient advocates and lawmakers is pushing for lower ratios, higher pay for workers and better access to personal protective equipment and “Nursing home residents died at higher rates than any other population during the They deserve better than this,” said Anna Doroghazi, advocacy director for AARP Fighting isolation State Kevin Kelly (R-Stratford), ranking member of the Senate Aging Committee, said he is pushing for a “patient-centered care bill of rights” that would guarantee that family members could visit, as long as facilities practiced safety “You know, as a loved one, when your family member is having difficulties,” he “You need your eyes and ears there to make sure everyone is doing what they’re supposed to ” State Catherine Abercrombie (D-Meriden), House chairwoman of the Human Services Committee, is among those who would like to see relaxed visitation rules for family “If the pandemic has shown us anything, it’s shown that the isolation for families and their loved ones has been detrimental to the health of the residents in these facilities,” she “I think with proper protocols, we could have done visitation ” A report that the state commissioned to examine its nursing home response found a percent increase in the number of residents reporting depressive symptoms between and There was also a rise in significant unplanned weight In addition to asking legislators to protect nursing home residents through improved staffing levels, continued virtual visitation, and permitting residents to install cameras in their rooms, AARP is continuing to push for programs that allow people to age at AARP Connecticut is collecting stories from family caregivers and nursing home residents impacted by Share your story at and learn more about AARP’s advocacy Natalie Missakian is a writer living in Cheshire .
